Activist Okiya Omtatah has been arrested at the Milimani law court for failing to appear for hearing of a criminal matter. Chief magistrate Francis Andayi ordered for his arrest in the case in which he is charged alongside other protesters. The magistrate had previously issued several warrants but the activist has never been arrested. Omtatah said he was following other matters at the High court and sent someone to tell the magistrate that he is held up. It was then that the judge ordered his arrest. He has been taken to Kilimani police station. Click here for the latest political news